@Node "Introduzione" "GMS_Mailer.guide/Introduction"
@Next "Il sistema"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc "Main"

Introduction
************

   GMS_Mailer is a mailer that send/receive e-mail and files from/to other
system (for example with a modem).

   GMS_Mailer features:

- Required OS 2.04 and MUI 2.1
- Full localized.
- Full 5D supports.
- Asynchronous mode.
- Caller ID supports.
- Supports these handshake protocols:

   YooHoo
   EMSI

- Supports these file transfer protocols:

   ZedZip
   ZedZap
   DirectZap
   Hydra

- FAX and VOICE supports.

- And more...

@EndNode

@Node "Il sistema" "GMS_Mailer.guide/The System"
@Next "Il modem"
@Prev "Introduzione"
@Toc "Main"

The System
**********

   GMS is distributed on many subdirectories of a single directory,
assigned as `GMS:'

        GMS:
         |
         + bin                  --> GMS_Mailer
         |
         + libs                 --> GMS.library GMS_Mailer.library ...
         |
         + config               --> Mailer[.x]/MailerSettings ...
         |
         + rexx                 --> CallNode.gms ...

   If you are a registered user, you must put the `GMS_Mailer.key' file in
the `GMS:' directory, for the program to properly recognize it.


@EndNode

@Node "Il modem" "GMS_Mailer.guide/The modem"
@Next "La configurazione"
@Prev "Il sistema"
@Toc "Main"

The modem
*********

   The modem must be Hayes compatible, because other modem command
standards are currently not supported.

   Take care that your modem should respond to successful connects with a
"CONNECT XXXX" message (where XXXX is the baudrate). If your modem returns
only "CONNECT", GMS_Mailer assumes that the connection takes place at 300 baud.

   Example modem settings:

 @{" US Robotics Courier HST Modems " Link "US Robotics"}
 @{" ZyXEL Modems " Link "ZyXEL"}
 @{" Internal Supra 2400zi Modems " Link "Supra 2400zi"}
 @{" 2400 Baud Modems " Link "2400 Baud"}

@EndNode

@Node "US Robotics" "GMS_Mailer.guide/The modem/US Robotics Courier HST Modems"
@Next "ZyXEL"
@Prev ""
@Toc "The modem"

US Robotics Courier HST Modems
******************************

   These are the settings for a Dual Standard HST modem.

   USRobotics Courier 14400 HST Dual Standard NRAM Settings...

       DIAL=PULSE  B1  F1  M3  X7
       BAUD=19200  PARITY=N  WORDLEN=8

       &A3  &B1  &G0  &H1  &I0  &J0  &K3  &L0
       &M4  &N0  &P0  &R2  &S0  &X0  &Y1

       S02=043   S03=013   S04=010   S05=008
       S06=007   S07=060   S08=002   S09=006
       S10=007   S11=070   S12=050   S13=001
       S15=008   S19=002   S21=010   S22=017
       S23=019   S24=150   S26=000   S27=000
       S28=008   S38=000

       STORED PHONE #0:
                    #1:
                    #2:
                    #3:

   To setup your modem, enter a terminal program. Select the baudrate at
which you want to "lock" your modem, and type:

       AT&FM3X7&A3&B1&H1&K3&R2S13=1S15=8&W 

   and press return. Your modem is now set up for use with GMS_Mailer.

   In your configuration file, use the lines:

       Baud=38400
       BaudLock=YES
       7Wire=YES
       SlowModem=10
       ModemInit=~~ATZ|
       ModemHangUp=|^
       ModemDialPre=~~ATDP
       ModemDialPost=|
       ModemAnswer=~~ATB0S7=30A|
       ArqString=ARQ
       SniffArq=YES

@EndNode

@Node "ZyXEL" "GMS_Mailer.guide/The modem/ZyXEL"
@Next "Supra 2400zi"
@Prev "US Robotics"
