ZyXEL Modems
************

   These are the settings for a ZyXEL 1496 E modem, ROMs 6.11a or higher.
If you have one of the other models, the parameters are the same.

   Current   Setting.............

        B0   E1   L1   M1   N1   Q0   V1   X7  
       &B1  &C1  &D3  &G0  &H3  &J0  &K4  &L0  &M0  &N0  &P0  &R1
                                                    &S0  &X0  &Y1
       *B0  *C0  *D0  *E0  *F0  *G0  *I0  *L0  *M0  *P9  *Q2  *S0  

       S00=000   S01=000   S02=043   S03=013   S04=010   
       S05=008   S06=003   S07=060   S08=002   S09=006   
       S10=015   S11=050   S12=000   S13=000   S14=002   
       S15=002   S16=000   S17=018   S18=000   S19=000   
       S20=001   S21=242   S22=000   S23=121   S24=034   
       S25=000   S26=000   S27=156   S28=068   S29=000   
       S30=000   S31=017   S32=019   S33=000   S34=030   
       S35=000   S36=000   S37=000   S38=008   S39=000   
       S40=000   S41=000   S42=002   S43=000   S44=000   
       S45=000   S46=000   S47=000   S48=004   S49=000   

   To setup your modem, enter a terminal program. Select the baudrate at
which you want to "lock" your modem, and type:

       AT&FX7&D3S42.1=1S48.2=1&W 

   and press return. Your modem is now set up for use with GMS_Mailer.

       In your configuration file, use the lines:

       Baud=38400
       BaudLock=YES
       7Wire=YES
       SlowModem=10
       ModemInit=~~ATZ|
       ModemHangUp=|^
       ModemDialPre=~~ATDP
       ModemDialPost=|
       ModemAnswer=~~ATA|
       ArqString=ARQ
       SniffArq=YES

@EndNode

@Node "Supra 2400zi" "GMS_Mailer.guide/The modem/Internal Supra 2400zi Modems"
@Next "2400 Baud"
@Prev "ZyXEL"
@Toc "The modem"

Internal Supra 2400zi Modems
****************************

   Set your modem to: 

       E1 L2 M1 Q0 V1 X4 B0 Y0
       &C1 &D3 &G0 &J0 &L0 &M0 &P0 &S0

       S0=0 S2=43 S3=13 S4=10 S5=8 S6=2 S7=20 S8=2 S9=6
       S10=14 S12=50 S25=5 S26=1

   To setup your modem, enter a terminal program that can talk to
"modem0.device" and set the baudrate to 2400 baud. Then type:

       AT&FE1Q0V1X4&C1&D3&S0&W 

   and press return. You modem is now set up for use with GMS_Mailer.

   In your configuration file, use the lines:

       SerialName=modem0.device
       Baud=2400
       SlowModem=10
       ModemInit=~~AT~Z|~
       ModemHangUp=|^
       ModemDialPre=~~AT~DP
       ModemDialPost=|~
       ModemAnswer=~~AT~A|~

@EndNode

@Node "2400 Baud" "GMS_Mailer.guide/The modem/2400 Baud Modems"
@Next ""
@Prev "Supra 2400zi"
@Toc "The modem"

2400 Baud Modems
****************

   Set your modem to: 

       E1  echo modem commands
       Q0  display result codes
       V1  verbose results
       X1  or highter
       &C1 DCD follows carrier detect
       &D3 reset ondtr drop
       &S0 DSR always on

   To setup your modem, enter a terminal program and set the baudrate to
2400 baud. Then type:

       AT&FE1Q0V1X4&C1&D3&S0&W

   and press return. You modem is now set up for use with GMS_Mailer.

   In your configuration file, use the lines 

       Baud=2400
       SlowModem=10
       ModemInit=~~AT~Z|~
       ModemHangUp=|^
       ModemDialPre=~~ATDP
       ModemDialPost=|~
       ModemAnswer=~~AT~A|~

@EndNode

@Node "La configurazione" "GMS_Mailer.guide/The configuration"
@Next "GMS_Mailer"
@Prev "Il modem"
@Toc "Main"

The configuration
*****************

 @{" MailerSettings " Link "MailerSettings"}
 @{" MailerEditor " Link "MailerEditor"}

   The configuration is made up by a set of ASCII files, located in the
`GMS:Config/' subdirectory. The format is very simple: a series of
`<field name>=<field value>', spread over one or more lines.

   It's not required to enter all the keywords available for each
configuration file: all uninitialized fields will assume a reasonable
default value, usually a null string or zero.

   `<field value>' is considered to end at the first blank space: if
you need to include a space in it you have two ways to do it. You can
enclose the whole value with quotes (`"'), or use the ``\'' (backslash
plus space) sequence instead of a space. Similar sequences (backslash
plus character), must always be used if you need to insert quote
symbols, or backslashes:

     Due Parole     -> "Due Parole"
     
     Due Parole     -> Due\ Parole
     
     "Due" Parole   -> "\"Due\" Parole"

   When you alter one of the configuration files, there is no warranty
that changes will be immediately used by the software; the configuration
is read only once at startup.  Before every change of configuration, then,
run the `Avail Flush' command to properly terminate execution.

   The configuration files will be put in a specific directory.

   For the phone line 0, you must put your configuration files in
`GMS:Config/Mailer/' directory.

   For the other phone lines you must put your configuration files in
`GMS:Config/Mailer.x' where 'x' is the number of the line.

   Examples:

GMS:Config/Mailer/               for default phone line
   MailerSettings
   MailerEditor

GMS:Config/Mailer.1/             for the phone line 1
   MailerSettings
   MailerEditor

GMS:Config/Mailer.39000/         for the phone line 39000
   MailerSettings
   MailerEditor

@EndNode

@Node "MailerSettings" "GMS_Mailer/The configuration/MailerSettings"
@Next "MailerEditor"
@Prev ""
@Toc "La configurazione"

MailerSettings
**************

   The file is `GMS:Config/Mailer[.x]/MailerSettings'.

 @{" AKAs " Link "cfgAKAs"}
 @{" BBS " Link "cfgBBS"}
 @{" External commands " Link "cfgComExt"}
 @{" Fax " Link "cfgFax"}
 @{" Voice " Link "cfgVoice"}
 @{" Handshakes " Link "cfgHandshakes"}
 @{" Log " Link "cfgLog"}
 @{" Modem " Link "cfgModem"}
 @{" Serial " Link "cfgSeriale"}
 @{" Protocols " Link "cfgProtocolli"}
 @{" Specials " Link "cfgSpeciali"}
 @{" System " Link "cfgSystem"}


   These keyword are used to setting defaults value.

      Answer=NO
      ModemInit=ATZ|
      ModemAnswer=ATA|
      ModemDialPre=ATDT
      ModemDialPost=|
      ModemHangUp=^
      SniffArq=NO

      7Wire=ON
      Baud=14400
      Dsr=ON
      Lock=ON
      MaxBaud=ON
      MinBaud=2400
      SerialName=serial.device
      SerialUnit=0
      SerialFlags=0
      Shared=NO
      SlowModem=10

      LocalizeLog=NO
      LocalizeLogDate=NO
      MaxLogLines=0
      MaxLogSecs=0

      LogScheduler=Discreet
      LogInformation=Discreet
      LogOutside=Discreet
      LogSecurity=Discreet
      LogSession=Discreet
      LogModem=Discreet
      LogSystem=Discreet
      LogTransfer=Discreet
      LogLink=Discreet
      LogDebugger=Discreet

      YooHoo=ON
      Emsi=ON

      ZedZip=ON
      ZedZap=ON
      DirectZap=ON
      Hydra=ON
      HydraBaud=2400

      DialTimeout=120
      RedialDelay=60
      Accounting=OFF

      ProcessOnly4D=OFF

      BiSendMail=All
      BiSendFlo=First
      BiSendRlo=First


@EndNode

